abstract: The Democrat from Massachusetts makes his first appearance on Capitol Hill since he began undergoing treatment for a brain tumor.
snippet: The Democrat from Massachusetts makes his first appearance on Capitol Hill since he began undergoing treatment for a brain tumor.
lead_paragraph: Senator Edward M. Kennedy of Massachusetts walked triumphantly into the Senate on Wednesday for the first time since learning that he had brain cancer, hoping to provide Democrats with the crucial, single vote that they need to reverse a cut in Medicare reimbursements to doctors.

abstract: After hearing from constituents, many lawmakers believe that they cannot afford an energy policy stalemate.
snippet: After hearing from constituents, many lawmakers believe that they cannot afford an energy policy stalemate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON  Senator Susan Collins, Republican of Maine, said anxiety over fuel oil costs is at crisis proportions in her state. Senator Amy Klobuchar, Democrat of Minnesota, said oil drilling advocates weighed in from the sidelines as she marched in a Fourth of July parade.
